# Test: SameDayPartialBnBShield
# Purpose: Same Day shield survives an earlier disposal's PARTIAL B&B use
# Rules Tested: Same Day, Bed & Breakfast, Section 104 Pooling
# Complexity: Medium
# Key Features: Two earlier disposals compete for one future buy whose same-day
#               SELL must keep its S105(1) reservation regardless of how much
#               the first earlier disposal actually B&B-matches.
# Expected Outcome: The Feb 10 same-day SELL of 30 matches the Feb 10 buy at
#                   £11 (not the S104 pool average). Pins TCGA92/S106A(9)/S105(1).
#
# Verification Notes:
#   shield(Feb 10) = min(same-day SELL 30, same-day BUY 50) = 30, leaving 20 of
#   the Feb 10 buy for B&B. Feb 1 (SELL 5) B&B-takes 5; Feb 3 (SELL 100)
#   B&B-takes 15 and 85 from the S104 pool. The Feb 10 buy is left with exactly
#   30 unreserved, which the Feb 10 same-day SELL claims in full.
#
#   Calculations:
#     Initial pool: 200 @ £10 = £2000, avg £10/share
#     Feb 1 SELL 5 @ £12:   5 B&B to Feb 10 @ £11 = £55 cost,  gain £5
#     Feb 3 SELL 100 @ £12: 15 B&B to Feb 10 @ £11 = £165 cost, gain £15
#                           85 S104 @ £10 = £850 cost,          gain £170
#     Feb 10 SELL 30 @ £11.50: 30 Same Day to Feb 10 @ £11 = £330 cost, gain £15
#     Holding after: 115 @ £10 = £1150 (Feb 10 buy fully matched, adds nothing)
#     Total 2023/24 gain: £5 + £185 + £15 = £205

2024-01-01 BUY ABC 200 @ 10.00 GBP

2024-02-01 SELL ABC 5 @ 12.00 GBP
2024-02-03 SELL ABC 100 @ 12.00 GBP

2024-02-10 BUY ABC 50 @ 11.00 GBP
2024-02-10 SELL ABC 30 @ 11.50 GBP
